Here's the full implementation plan I've created, broken into 11 phases:

Phase 1 — Project Scaffolding

Initialize Next.js 14+ with App Router and TypeScript
Set up Tailwind CSS with Midas's dark color palette (#0A0A0F backgrounds, #00D4FF accent, etc.)
Install core deps: viem, recharts, lucide-react
Configure fonts: Space Grotesk (headings), IBM Plex Mono (addresses/data)
Phase 2 — Core Lib Layer

lib/constants.ts — contract addresses, role hashes (MINTER_ROLE, BURNER_ROLE), known address labels
lib/contracts.ts — ABIs (ERC-20, AccessControl, Oracle, Midas-specific)
lib/viem-client.ts — public client connected to Ethereum mainnet via Alchemy
lib/etherscan.ts — API wrapper for token txs, holders, event logs
lib/decoder.ts — ABI decoder utilities using viem's decodeFunctionData
lib/formatters.ts — number formatting, address truncation
Phase 3 — Shared Components

Navbar.tsx — top nav with 5 tab links + connection indicator
AddressTag.tsx — truncated address (0xABCD...1234) with copy-to-clipboard
StatusBadge.tsx — status indicators (success, warning, error)
Root layout.tsx — dark theme shell, font loading, nav integration
Phase 4 — Custom Hooks

useTokenData.ts — fetches totalSupply, NAV price, holder count, calculates AUM
useTransactions.ts — fetches mint/burn Transfer events from Etherscan
useRoles.ts — checks hasRole() for addresses against Midas contracts
Phase 5 — Tab 1: Token Overview & NAV Monitor

Token cards for mTBILL and mBASIS (NAV, supply, holders, 24h change)
Portfolio summary card (total AUM, total holders, product count)
NAV price history line chart (30 days, Recharts)
Auto-refresh every 60 seconds with visible countdown
Phase 6 — Tab 2: Transaction Monitor (HIGHEST PRIORITY)

Sortable mint/burn transaction table
Smart contract function decoder (paste tx hash → decoded calldata)
Expandable transaction detail panel
Filters: token (mTBILL/mBASIS/All), type (Mint/Burn/All), date range
Etherscan links for every tx hash
Phase 7 — Tab 3: Whitelist & Access Control Manager

Contract roles table (admin, minter, burner with active addresses)
Address lookup: check balances, roles, interaction history
Whitelist simulation form (generates mock calldata + gas estimate)
Recent RoleGranted/RoleRevoked event feed
Phase 8 — Tab 4: Block Explorer & Wallet Analyzer

Top holders table with % of supply
Holder concentration pie chart
Wallet deep dive (balances, ETH balance, interaction timeline)
Daily net mint/burn volume bar chart
Phase 9 — Tab 5: Operational Runbook

6 interactive workflow diagrams (Subscription, Redemption, Product Launch, Whitelist Update, NAV Update, Incident Response)
Interactive operational checklists
Auto-detected risk flags (oracle staleness from real data)
Phase 10 — Polish & Deploy

Loading skeletons, error handling, responsive tweaks
.env.local setup for API keys
Deploy to Vercel with live URL
Phase 11 — Git: Push to GitHub

Commit everything and push to https://github.com/zeewaqar1234/Midas-Operations-Dashboard